description: Back-formation from xylography, corresponding to xylo- (“wood”) +‎ -graph.

entries.meaning: An engraving in wood or woodcut, especially one used in printing predating the Western tradition (14th c.).
A print taken from such an engraving.

verbs.description: xylograph (third-person singular simple present xylographs, present participle xylographing, simple past and past participle xylographed)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To make a print from an engraving in wood.
